Nigeria’s number one man, President Muhammadu Buhari has sympathized with the Eze Nelson Nmerengwa of the Isieketa Ancient Kingdom in Isiala Ngwa South Local Government of Abia State over the passing of his mother, Comfort, aged 105.  The president, in a condolence message released by his spokesman, Mr Femi Adesina, on Thursday in Abuja, affirmed that the deceased could be said to have lived a glorious life, crowned with longevity.He said: “But the thing about mothers is that however old they are, we never want to see them leave.“Mothers are from Heaven, and Nma has only returned home.”He urged Nmerengwa and members of the Isieketa Ancient Kingdom to take solace in the quality of life lived by the departed and the legacy she left behind.The president applauded the reputation of Nma as a dedicated Christian, farmer, community leader, and loving mother to all her children, encouraging the family to keep the memory of their matriarch aglow through a continuation of her good works.Buhari prayed to God to accept Nma’s soul and give her peaceful rest.  source By Ismaila Chafe     Abuja   -      President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated the Isi Ala 1 of Isieketa Ancient Kingdom, His Majesty Eze Nelson Nmerengwa, who turns 60 years on July 27. The President’s congratulatory message is in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki has expressed shock over the death of the mother of the Emir of Ilorin, late Alhaja Aishat Nma Zuluqarnain Gambari. Saraki I have just received with immeasurable pain the news of the passing unto glory of… In "News" Daura (Katsina State) -   Hajiya Rakiya Adamu, the only surviving sister of President Muhammadu Buhari, has appealed to Nigerians to pray for the President, instead of spreading rumours about his health. She made the appeal in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Daura, Katsina State,… In "Top Stories"